    "recap_headline": "University of Louisiana at Lafayette Athletics",
    "recap_text": "LAFAYETTE \u2013\nThe Louisiana Ragin' Cajuns jumped out to an early 8-1 lead and rode 11 hits and a season-high eight stolen bases to claim an 11-7 win over UTRGV on Tuesday at M.L. \"Tigue\" Moore Field at Russo Park, giving head coach\nMatt Deggs\nhis 200th win as the Cajuns' skipper.\nLee Amedee\n,\nDonovan LaSalle\n,\nDrew Markle\nand\nColt Brown\neach had two hits to pace the Cajuns' offensive attack, with Amedee stretching his hitting streak to nine games, while LaSalle increased his streak to eight.\nThe Cajuns benefitted in their running game by swiping eight bases in the contest \u2013 all within the first three innings of the game \u2013 with Amedee and Markle leading the way with two steals each. LaSalle,\nRigoberto Hernandez\n,\nSteven Spalitta\nand Brown \u2013 who extended his hit streak to eight games \u2013 stole one base each.\nTy Roman\n(1-2), making a designated short start, worked 3.1 innings for his first win as a Cajun. Roman allowed six hits and three runs with one walk and four strikeouts in his 65-pitch outing.\nParker Smith\n, the fourth of five Cajuns' pitchers, had three scoreless innings, allowing just one hit.\nThe Vaqueros (7-10) had 13 hits in the contest, with second baseman Thomas Williams pacing UTRGV with three hits and two runs scored. Easton Moomau drove in three runs to pace UTRGV in that department.\nThe Vaqueros got on the board first, getting three hits, highlighted by Julius Ramirez's RBI single, before the Cajuns (13-4) struck back with two in the bottom of the first. Markle had a bunt single with one out and, after Amedee walked, the two moved up on a double steal.\nHernandez had an RBI groundout before Brown doubled home Amedee to give the Cajuns a lead they would not relinquish.\nThe Cajuns added four more runs in the second, highlighted by an RBI single by Markle and Amedee's double down the left field line, and plated two more in the third, with runs scoring on a wild pitch and\nGriffin Hebert's\nRBI groundout.\nAn RBI single by Chayton Fischer and an Ethan Edinger sacrifice got two runs home for the Vaqueros in the fourth before Garrett Carter got the final two outs.\nLouisiana got a run back on Amedee's second hit of the game, but UTRGV touched Carter for two more runs in the fifth to cut the lead to 9-5. The Cajuns scored twice in the seventh before the Vaqueros got four straight hits in the ninth inning for the final score.\nThe win was the sixth in the last seven games for the Cajuns, who will open Sun Belt Conference play when they host long-time rival South Alabama for a three-game series beginning Friday at 6 p.m.\nFans are encouraged to stay engaged with the Ragin' Cajuns by downloading the #GeauxCajuns app. Click\nhere\nfor iOS/Apple platforms and\nhere\nfor Android platforms.\nFor the latest updates on Ragin' Cajuns baseball, follow on Facebook (RaginCajunsBaseball), Twitter (@RaginCajunsBSB) and Instagram (@RaginCajunsBSB) or check RaginCajuns.com."
  },
